[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm having trouble with the following <code>isDefEq</code> query between two terms that are identical, except for a subterm replaced with a metavariable:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Lean</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Meta</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Expr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Elab</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Tactic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Core</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">axiom</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Unit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∃</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Unit</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">True</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">noncomputable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">concrete</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">p</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choose</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- set_option trace.Meta.isDefEq true</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">eval</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">getConstInfo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">``concrete</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">value!</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bindingBody!</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">instantiate1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">``Unit.unit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[])</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">bindingBody!</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">instantiate1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mkFreshExprMVar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Expr</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ss\">``Unit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[]))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">withConfig</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">proofIrrelevance</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">false</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">isDefEq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">dbg_trace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">instantiateMVars</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e2</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"o\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Looking at the trace, the metavariable is never assigned, probably due to proof irrelevance. However, I've specifically set <code>proofIrrelevance</code> to <code>false</code> in the <code>Config</code>. Is there a way that I can get a more syntactic match in this case?</p>",
        "id": 531254987,
        "sender_full_name": "Chase Norman",
        "timestamp": 1753667822
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Isn't this due to choose being opaque?</p>",
        "id": 531262375,
        "sender_full_name": "Justin Asher",
        "timestamp": 1753671445
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe it's applying subsingleton elimination?</p>",
        "id": 531290748,
        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1753686364
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It looks like <code>isDefEqArgsFirstPass</code> in ExprDefEq implicitly encodes proof irrelevance. When proof arguments are being compared, then the arguments are completely skipped if neither is of the form <code>fun x_1 ... x_n =&gt; ?m y_1 ... y_m</code>, where <code>n</code> and <code>m</code> can be 0. Here, <code>p () =?= p ?_</code> is being skipped.</p>\n<p>It's probably worth creating an issue.</p>",
        "id": 531305027,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1753690845
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"306601\">@Kyle Miller</span>  for the really helpful analysis. I have created an issue here: <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/issues/9612\">https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/issues/9612</a>.</p>\n<p><span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span>'s on the issue are appreciated, as well as ideas for how to work around the issue. I'd like to release a feature for Canonical that depends on a guarantee that a successful <code>isDefEq</code> query between a term with metavariables and a term without metavariables always assigns all of the metavariables, even if they are in proof arguments.</p>",
        "id": 531504690,
        "sender_full_name": "Chase Norman",
        "timestamp": 1753760592
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's my workaround:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">isDefEqForce</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Expr</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MetaM</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Bool</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">do</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">isDefEqForce</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;&amp;&amp;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">isDefEqForce</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">isDefEqGuarded</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">u</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">v</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 531648719,
        "sender_full_name": "Chase Norman",
        "timestamp": 1753805444
    }
